  <wpt lon="-4.56126416741386" lat="57.43671993087683">
    <name>Aigas Gorge </name>
    <cmt>Kilmorack Community Council has a sign in Aigas power station car park asking paddlers to avoid the gorge from March to 15th of August! This is to protect the gorge’s wildlife particularly nesting birds such as ospreys!  Out of this period if you decide to carry on with your rafting through the gorge, you must be aware that the Aigas power station also has a sight near the dam warning paddlers of “Extreme Increase in Surface Currents May Occur At Any Time” the point this route takes you off the river Beauly and back on the track on your wheels is one mile to the dam, which is very safe distance!</cmt>
    <desc>Kilmorack Community Council has a sign in Aigas power station car park asking paddlers to avoid the gorge from March to 15th of August! This is to protect the gorge’s wildlife particularly nesting birds such as ospreys!  Out of this period if you decide to carry on with your rafting through the gorge, you must be aware that the Aigas power station also has a sight near the dam warning paddlers of “Extreme Increase in Surface Currents May Occur At Any Time” the point this route takes you off the river Beauly and back on the track on your wheels is one mile to the dam, which is very safe distance!</desc>
